# What is Linux?
  -Linux is a Operting system just like Mac-OS and Windows that is more light in weight.
  -Linux is an umbrella term for many Operating systems.

# Nano :-
  It is easy to get started with Nano! To create or edit a file using nano, 
  we simply use nano filename -- replacing "filename" with the name of the file you wish to edit.

# VIM
  VIM is a much more advanced text editor. Whilst you're not expected to know all advanced features,
  it's helpful to mention it for powering up your Linux skills.

 Commands                    Description
1. echo          -            Output any text we provide
2. whoami        -            Finds out what user are we logged in as
3. ls            -            Listing directries/files
4. cd            -            Change directory
5. cat           -            Concatenate
6. pwd           -            Print Working directory
7. find          -            Search Files
8. grep          -            Search contents of a file with a specific value
9. grep -R       -            Recrusively
10. &            -            Run commands in background
11. &&           -            Run multiple commands at once
12. >            -            This operator is Redirector 
!3. >>           -            Same as > but appends insteaed of replacing
14. ssh          -            Allows remote execution of the commands
15. man          -            Manual
16. touch        -            Create file
17. mkdir        -            Create folder
18. cp           -            Copy
19. mv           -            Remove
20. file         -            Determine type of file
